# BDS component & catalog governance

This package (`bds`) is the **only** source of truth for Bluetab DS components. The Phoenix storybook app (`../storybook`) and the Vite HTML catalog (`assets/index.html`) both consume it.

## Catalog pipeline (do not bypass)

```
assets/src/catalog.js  --export:catalog-->  priv/catalog.json  -->  Bds.Catalog  -->  storybook HomeLive
        |                                                                                      |
        +---- main.js renders index.html (Vite dev catalog) -----------------------------------+
```

- **Author catalog metadata in** `assets/src/catalog.js` (`COMPONENTS`, `GROUP_ORDER`, `snippets`).
- **Never** hand-edit `priv/catalog.json` except to debug export; regenerate with `npm run export:catalog`.
- **Never** duplicate component lists or example HTML in storybook or other apps.

## Required files per catalog component change

| Step | File / action |
|------|----------------|
| Metadata + HTML examples | `assets/src/catalog.js` |
| Export for Elixir | `cd assets && npm run export:catalog` |
| Live preview (storybook) | `lib/bds/catalog/preview/bulk.ex` ‚Äî `render/3` for `component_id` |
| HEEx copy snippet | `lib/bds/catalog/snippets/bulk.ex` ‚Äî key `"id:index"` |
| Component API | `lib/bds/components.ex` or `lib/bds/components/*.ex` |
| Styles | `assets/src/css/components/*.css` (and related `main` imports) |
| Interactions | `assets/src/` JS if behavior is shared |

If `Bds.Catalog.Preview` falls back to `raw(@html)`, live storybook preview still works but **add Bulk render + HEEx snippet** for any `bt_*` example.

## Verification

1. `mix test test/bds/catalog_test.exs`
2. `cd assets && npm run dev` ‚Äî browse `index.html` sidebar and examples
3. In storybook: recompile and open `/` ‚Äî must match Vite catalog navigation and content

## Semantics

- `id` in `catalog.js` is stable public API (URLs, tests). Renaming requires coordinated updates in preview/snippets/tests.
- Catalog `title`, `description`, `group`, and `examples[].title` must be **English Gettext msgids**; Phoenix apps display them via `Bds.Catalog.localize/1` or `gettext/1`.
- `examples[].html` is the **HTML/CSS catalog** truth; HEEx in snippets must describe the same example for Phoenix consumers.
- New groups require `GROUP_ORDER` in `catalog.js`.

## Consumers

- **storybook**: path dep `{:bds, path: "../bds"}` ‚Äî no local catalog fork
- **npm package**: `npm run build:lib` runs export + vite build

When storybook work needs a component change, **change BDS in this repo**, export catalog, then validate storybook ‚Äî not the reverse.
